%md
## Predictive Maintenance on Oracle DBMS 20c
Demo Zeppelin Notebook to evaluate MSET-SPRT anomaly detection algorithm. 
First of all download the **Bearing Data Set** from [NASA Ames Prognostics Data Repository](https://ti.arc.nasa.gov/tech/dash/groups/pcoe/prognostic-data-repository/) and merge files in the directory: **/1st_test** in two CSV parts: Train (from Oct,22 to Nov,1) and Test (from Nov,2 to Nov,25).
Then execute following statements SQL and import files:
```
CREATE TABLE MSET_TRAINING_SH_DATA 
   (	"TIME_ID" TIMESTAMP (6) NOT NULL ENABLE, 
	"B11" NUMBER, 
	"B12" NUMBER, 
	"B21" NUMBER, 
	"B22" NUMBER, 
	"B31" NUMBER, 
	"B32" NUMBER, 
	"B41" NUMBER, 
	"B42" NUMBER
   );
   
CREATE TABLE MSET_TEST_SH_DATA AS MSET_TRAINING_SH_DATA;
```

First of all download the Bearing Data Set from NASA Ames Prognostics Data Repository and merge files in the directory: /1st_test in two CSV parts: Train (from Oct,22 to Nov,1) and Test (from Nov,2 to Nov,25).
Then execute following statemente SQL and import files:

CREATE TABLE MSET_TRAINING_SH_DATA 
   (	"TIME_ID" TIMESTAMP (6) NOT NULL ENABLE, 
	"B11" NUMBER, 
	"B12" NUMBER, 
	"B21" NUMBER, 
	"B22" NUMBER, 
	"B31" NUMBER,

	"B41" NUMBER,

CREATE TABLE MSET_TEST_SH_DATA AS MSET_TRAINING_SH_DATA;

paragraphs.title: Comparison among normal - failure signals
paragraphs.text:
%osql
SELECT * FROM
(SELECT mset_training_sh_data.b31 as b31_norm, ROWNUM AS rownum_a
FROM mset_training_sh_data where time_id>to_timestamp('2003-10-22 01:11:24','yyyy-mm-dd hh24:mi:ss') 
) ALIAS_A,
(SELECT time_id,mset_test_sh_data.b31 as b31_fail, ROWNUM AS rownum_b
FROM mset_test_sh_data where time_id>to_timestamp('2003-11-25 23:11:24','yyyy-mm-dd hh24:mi:ss') ) ALIAS_B
WHERE ALIAS_A.rownum_a = ALIAS_B.rownum_b

paragraphs.title: % number of anomalies detected vs samples
paragraphs.text:
%osql
select to_number(dt) as dt ,sample,fail_num,trunc(((fail_num/sample)*100),2) as "%_fails_detected" 
from
    ( select dt as dt1,count(b11) as sample 
      from (
             select to_char(time_id,'DD') as dt,b11 
             from mset_test_sh_data
             ) 
      where dt > '09'
      group by dt order by dt),pred_stat_temp 

where pred_stat_temp.dt=dt1 order by dt

%md
### Evaluation on trigger date

%md
create table pred_stat as 
select dt,count(pred) as fail_num from (
SELECT  to_char(time_id,'DD') as dt,b11,b31,
       PREDICTION(mset_model1 using *) OVER (ORDER BY time_id) pred 
       --PREDICTION_DETAILS(mset_model using *) OVER (ORDER BY time_id) anomalyDetails       
  FROM mset_test_sh_data
  WHERE time_id >=  to_timestamp ('2003-11-19 21:16:07','yyyy-mm-dd hh24:mi:ss') AND time_id <=  to_timestamp ('2003-11-24 01:01:25','yyyy-mm-dd hh24:mi:ss') and mod(to_number(to_char(time_id,'FF')),2)=0
  )  where pred=0 group by dt order by dt

create table pred_stat as
select dt,count(pred) as fail_num from (
SELECT to_char(time_id,‘DD’) as dt,b11,b31,
PREDICTION(mset_model1 using *) OVER (ORDER BY time_id) pred
–PREDICTION_DETAILS(mset_model using *) OVER (ORDER BY time_id) anomalyDetails
FROM mset_test_sh_data
WHERE time_id >= to_timestamp (‘2003-11-19 21:16:07’,‘yyyy-mm-dd hh24:mi:ss’) AND time_id <= to_timestamp (‘2003-11-24 01:01:25’,‘yyyy-mm-dd hh24:mi:ss’) and mod(to_number(to_char(time_id,‘FF’)),2)=0
) where pred=0 group by dt order by dt
